BT 34.016 630.659 Td 1.159 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(This research area tackles with applications and enabling technologies for ubiquitous and wearable computing )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 616.403 Td 0.000 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(\(such as ad hoc networking technologies\).)] TJ ET
BT 34.016 590.147 Td 2.846 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(In ubiquitous computing a user has access to many computing devices. These computing devices will be )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 575.891 Td 0.215 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(unobtrusive and provide seamless access to a wide variety of data and allow the user to perform tasks as needed, )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 561.635 Td 1.180 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(where needed. The objective of ubiquitous computing is to move interaction with computers out of a person's )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 547.379 Td 3.254 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(central focus and into the user's peripheral attention where they can be used subconsciously. Ubiquitous )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 533.123 Td 0.000 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(computing is often characterized by the attributes of mobility, interconnectivity and context-awareness.)] TJ ET
BT 34.016 506.867 Td 0.392 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(One of the key attributes of ubiquitous computing is mobility. An individual will carry or wear multiple devices )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 492.611 Td 3.149 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(and move about the office, home or public places. It's obvious that these devices should be both easily )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 478.355 Td 1.172 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(transportable and simple to interact with. User interfaces, whether voice, pen based or key based, will present )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 464.099 Td 1.837 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(particular challenges in mobile devices. Frugality will be important when mobile devices are designed since )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 449.843 Td 0.760 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(resources of mobile devices are minimal. Displays of mobile devices have limited graphics capabilities and are )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 435.587 Td 0.000 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(quite small. Similarly, memory is limited, disks may be nonexistent, and software availability may be restricted.)] TJ ET
BT 34.016 409.331 Td 1.923 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(Another key attribute of ubiquitous computing is interconnectivity. Current mobile hosts such as notebooks, )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 395.075 Td 2.837 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(PDAs and cellular phones provide connectivity but lack interconnectivity. With these devices a user may )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 380.819 Td 1.351 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(connect to another system on a point to point basis. The ubiquitous computing paradigm will take this a step )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 366.563 Td 1.659 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(further. "Ubiquitous" devices, like existing devices, will have the ability to connect to systems on a point to )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 352.307 Td 1.299 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(point basis. They will have additional capabilities too. Devices will be aware of each other and know how to )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 338.051 Td 1.649 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(exchange information among themselves. In addition, they will be able to control each other as needed. Just )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 323.795 Td 0.572 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(how this will be accomplished remains to be seen. Suggestions including the use of infrared \(IrDA\), low power )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 309.539 Td 0.000 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(RF, or even inductive \(EMF\) communications have been proffered.)] TJ ET
BT 34.016 283.283 Td 1.315 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(For Ubiquitous devices to be truly useful they must support the concept of context awareness. Context aware )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 269.027 Td 1.022 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(devices will be able to adapt their behavior to the environment in which they find themselves. Devices should )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 254.771 Td 1.005 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(recognize when they transition to a new network or one that uses a different protocol and adapt appropriately; )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 240.515 Td 0.747 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(e.g. switch from using low power RF for communication to using an IrDA port instead. Context aware devices )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 226.259 Td 1.274 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(will also recognize the software, hardware and other resource constraints of devices they are interacting with. )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 212.003 Td 0.153 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(For example, a device should know or be able to discover whether a device it wishes to interact with can support )] TJ ET
BT 34.016 197.747 Td 0.000 Tw /F2 12.0 Tf  [(a certain protocol or windowing system. This is often referred to as resource qualification.)] TJ ET
